sevrices are located in: /etc/init.d
to deal with the particular service: ./<file>

to see the status of the particular service: netstat -nltup or <file> status

commmands: force-reload , reload ,restart , stop , --full-restart

some srvcs can also be found at /usr/lib/systemd/system

for old linux: service command and new as systemctl also
service --status-all

systemctl --type=service --status=running
systemctl list units
systemctl status apache2.service


ANTIVIRUS: 
sudo apt install clamav*
freshclam - to update the db of the antivirus	

only for parent folder to scan: clamscan <folder>
use -r to scan every sub dir
-i to list infected file

--remove
